Sentencas: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells were manufactured by plasma spraying the cell layers on porous ferritic stainless steel supports.
Titulo: Atmospheric Plasma-Sprayed Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Varying Cathode Microstructures

Sentencas: Cathodes with four different microstructures were produced by varying the plasma spray parameters and mixing carbon or starch-based pore forming agents with the ceramic feedstock powders.
Titulo: Atmospheric Plasma-Sprayed Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Varying Cathode Microstructures

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C, the best-performing button cell contained a cathode made with a carbon pore forming agent.
Titulo: Atmospheric Plasma-Sprayed Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Varying Cathode Microstructures

Sentencas: This cell had an open circuit potential of 1.057 V and peak power density of 562 mW/cm(2).
Titulo: Atmospheric Plasma-Sprayed Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Varying Cathode Microstructures

Sentencas: The lowest cell polarization resistance was 0.29 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C, measured at an operating point of 0.7 V. (C) 2017 The Electrochemical Society.
Titulo: Atmospheric Plasma-Sprayed Metal-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Varying Cathode Microstructures
